Infrastructure Change Management - Leading Bank
Infrastructure Change Management - Leading Bank
Location:  Singapore
Salary:  SGD90000 - SGD110000 per annumIf you are a highly motivated individual who enjoys working in a fast paced environment, this is an opportunity for you. You should have the experience of managing change process in the IT Infrastructure space with minimal disruption to the service availability. You would be planning, managing, reviewing and assessing IT Infrastructure changes, and the risks and impact involved. You are also required to coach junior team members with your wealth of experience
Requirements:
More than 8 years of experience in diverse areas of IT Infrastructure (such as Systems, Network, Storage, Databases, Data Centre etc)
Strong understanding and experience in change management, review and control processes
Strong knowledge and practical experience in ITSM
To succeed in this role, you must have a belief that you can make things happen. You are passionate about innovation and making a change. You must have demonstrated excellent communicative and interpersonal skills to interface with the various IT and business stakeholders.
Find out how you can play an integral role in this leading bank by sending your updated resume in MS Word format to Nate Goh. Look forward to an attractive remuneration package and the chance to further your career.
